5:
Listen up, everybody! We have all of
the materials we need. Now all that's
left is to finish strong with our
preparations!
9:
Since the seniors will be leaving the
school to us after they graduate,
we've got to give this our all!
13:
Heh, the future is a merciless
master. The relentless shifting of the
sands of time stops for no one...
save me, that is.
17:
As such, I have big plans. My destiny
is to found my own academy of
magic in the Endless Blue with
Couette and the other mages.
20:
Ah, about that. I'm afraid I'll have to
pass. Rakisha invited me to the
Kingdom of Sand, so I'll be going
there instead.
29:
Nothing against you, mind. This is
strictly business. I can teach
elemental magic while I conduct my
research. Plus, who could pass up
the opportunity to see the Titan?
34:
Not a thing's going to change with
me. Though, aside from the influx of
new students, I have had to clean
up after my bumbling idiot of an
ex-husband.
37:
Terrorizing and brainwashing
adventurers... That flimsy fop of a
man will have to answer for his
actions someday.
40:
Which reminds me... Reylas. If you
wanted to teach that sorry sack a
lesson, I won't stop you.
44:
It's true that I haven't forgiven
him—and I don't think I ever will.
47:
...But I've gotten back all of that
which I once lost. What's important
now is that I focus on the future.
50:
That's why I want to devote myself
to my research, alongside my
brother and family.
53:
I'm really looking forward to your
book, Stella. I can't wait to get a
copy so that I can brag about all of
you to everyone back home.
57: Thank you. I won't let you down.
62:
Not much to tell about the Guild
Knights, really. For better or worse,
we'll be the same as we ever were.
Probably have our hands full
patrolling the town as usual.
65:
But speaking of future prospects,
Keira and Finn have been doing
their part—and then some. I hear
they have big plans in the works
with the gang in Shibuya, too.
69:
Since the city's police force is finally
starting to get back on its feet,
they're thinking about forming an
alliance with us.
73:
And new recruits are coming in
every day. Perhaps our days of
being shorthanded will soon be
behind us.
77:
All that hard work is finally paying
off, but we can't start slacking now.
We'll man the helm until the next
generation is ready to take the lead.
82: Us? That should be obvious, missy!
87:
We're joining the Abyss Exploration
Team! We'll be core members of the
main squad. Oooh, I can hardly wait!
91:
Heehee... Can't take my eyes off of
them for a second, can I? I certainly
have my work cut out for me.
95:
It'll be a chance for you to use those
lamps of yours! You should be
happy we rely on you.
99:
That's not the compliment you think
it is, Leon...
103:
My duty remains the same. I shall
continue to act as a bridge between
the Vesta and the peoples of other
worlds.
105:
Some of the Vesta will be joining the
Abyss Exploration Team as well, so—
109:
We're gonna need every trick in the
book to survive. And since the Vesta
are world-hopping experts, I know
we can count on them in a pinch.
111:
Won't make them do all the work,
though. We'll lead the vanguard and
see to it that everyone gets home in
one piece.
116:
Thank you. I'm counting on you to
keep my people safe.
122:
...So, does that mean you'll be
heading to Tiatha instead of the
Farlands?
125:
Indeed, I'll be off. I received word
from Quade that the Star Augurs are
on the move once again.
128:
Ever since I decided to continue my
crusade as a Swallow Knight, I knew
that someday I would have to set off
on my own.
133:
As for me, I shall return to the
Farlands with Her Holiness. We have
people to serve. As such, we belong
in our kingdom.
139:
This was my own decision, but still...
With Oxtan, and the holy temple...
The thought alone makes me feel
like I'm gonna hurl...
143:
*sniffle* Wahhh... Can't... Can't I take
Lady Stella back to the kingdom with
me?! I'll set her up a nice little shrine
and worship her every day—I
promise!
152:
You have to promise! NO, swear!
PLEAAASE!
Nnn... WAHHHHH!
158:
*sniff* No... I mustn't cry. Just... stay
strong...
163:
Come now, this isn't goodbye for
good. We'll return to the Farlands
and Starview Village with valuable
information before you know it.
169:
Luckily for you, I'll be staying behind
in Palpebra to relay
communications between our
worlds. So you can bet your last coin
that my network shall be second to
none!
172:
After all, we want to keep up good
relations. Naturally, I'm the perfect
man for the job.
176:
We'll be sure to keep Starview
Village in the loop when it comes to
the Star Augurs. But, I'm curious
Alk—what are your plans?
179:
I'm not going to coddle you like
Nimbus or Sho would. Don't expect
me to stand back and let you bury
your head in the sand.
182:
But then again, that wouldn't be like
you. I'm sure you have a plan or two
up your sleeve.
187: ...You give me way too much credit.
191:
All right then, keep your secrets. I'll
be setting off after this so-called
"graduation ceremony". Of course, I'll
be taking part in the prep team's
"wrap party" as well.
194:
Speaking of parties... Have you had
your first real drink yet, Alk?
202:
I'd advise you to test your limits
before the celebrations begin. I'm
sure many will want to raise a glass
with you.
207:
Don't worry. I doubt anyone will
actually force me to drink.
218: Are you going to get drunk?
221:
Well... I mean, I don't want to make a
fool of myself or anything.
